20 ABLE Savings Program as a qualified program under federal law. (NRS
21 427A.882-427A.896)
22 Existing federal and state law provide that under certain circumstances, the
23 Department is required to recover benefits correctly paid under Medicaid from the
24 estate of a deceased person who received those benefits or any recipient of money
25 or property from the estate of such a deceased person. (42 U.S.C. § 1396p; NRS
26 422.29302) Under existing federal law, upon the death of the designated
27 beneficiary of an ABLE Account, a state is authorized to file a claim for payment
28 from the ABLE Account to recover benefits paid under Medicaid on behalf of the
29 designated beneficiary that are recoverable by the state. (26 U.S.C. § 529A(f))
30 Sections 1 and 3 of this bill provide that unless federal law otherwise requires,
31 the Department or any other officer or agency of State Government is prohibited
32 from seeking to recover benefits correctly paid under Medicaid for a designated
33 beneficiary of an ABLE Account: (1) from any money remaining in the ABLE
34 Account upon the death of the designated beneficiary; or (2) by filing a claim for
35 recovery from the ABLE Account. Section 1 additionally requires the Director of
36 the Department to apply for any necessary federal approval to carry out these
37 provisions. Section 2 of this bill authorizes the Director to administer the
38 provisions of section 1 in the same manner that the Director administers existing
39 law governing the recovery of benefits paid under Medicaid.
40 Section 4 of this bill provides that upon the passage and approval of this bill,
41 the Department and any other officer or agency of the State Government are
42 required to terminate any attempt to recover Medicaid benefits from an ABLE
43 Account, unless recovery from an ABLE Account is required by federal law.
